Edit `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/tranquility/page.module.css`.

Read the file first. Then make these changes:

1. Find `.stateProcessing` and all its nested rules. ADD a duplicate/alias block `.stateThinking` with identical styles right after `.stateProcessing` (keep `.stateProcessing` as well for now in case anything still references it).

2. After the last state block (`.stateSpeaking`), ADD two new state blocks:

```css
/* followup state */
.stateFollowup .omegaGlow {
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(99,210,190,0.35) 0%, rgba(16,185,129,0.12) 50%, transparent 75%);
}
.stateFollowup .omegaSymbol {
  color: rgba(99, 210, 190, 0.92);
  text-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(99, 210, 190, 0.8), 0 0 60px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
}

/* error state */
.stateError .omegaGlow {
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(239,68,68,0.25) 0%, rgba(239,68,68,0.08) 50%, transparent 75%);
}
.stateError .omegaSymbol {
  color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.7);
  text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.5);
}
```

That's all. Do not change anything else in the file.

